15:51.560 --> 15:55.004
It says, Judah is a lion's cub.

15:55.345 --> 15:56.967
From the prey, my son, you've gone up.

15:57.007 --> 15:57.788
He stooped down.

15:57.848 --> 16:02.333
He crouched as a lion and as a lioness who dares, aroused him.

16:02.353 --> 16:09.362
The scepter shall not depart from Judah, nor the ruler's staff from between his feet until tribute comes to him.

16:09.570 --> 16:12.434
To him shall be the obedience of the peoples."

16:14.296 --> 16:20.705
So this image kind of shifts to this image of this beast and this kingdom.

16:21.366 --> 16:29.336
And the first thing we see here is this lion's cub, which is obviously a young lion that's rising in its strength and power.

16:30.157 --> 16:35.665
