And you see this here at the end of verse 10, these tributes that are coming to Him and the obedience of the peoples, that's beyond just Jewish peoples, that's all the peoples coming to Him.

21:12.141 --> 21:13.242
All the peoples come to Him.

21:13.262 --> 21:18.127
This is a prophetic promise to Judah to show us who Jesus is and what He's come to do.

21:19.749 --> 21:20.850
That Jesus is God.

21:21.698 --> 21:30.889
that he's come to bring all creation under his authority, back under his protection as the Lion King, to expand his kingdom until it covers the earth and renews all creation.

21:31.870 --> 21:40.721
Right, just as a king is domain and people in it, so Jesus has people in it and he's building that kingdom until it covers the earth.

21:43.064 --> 21:46.628
And as God, he is the one who can actually do this.

21:47.670 --> 21:51.154
He isn't bringing just temporary renewal, just those

21:51.330 --> 21:55.776
moments of beauty and glory, He's bringing that to bear to the ends of the earth.

21:57.739 --> 22:08.133
Jesus is God and He is God the Lion King, who's come strong and mighty to expand His kingdom in this earth.

22:09.194 --> 22:17.626
So maybe at least another question could be this, is how is He able to actually accomplish this?

22:17.766 --> 22:19.629
How is He accomplishing this in this world?

22:19.669 --> 22:20.690
Because clearly

22:20.770 --> 22:23.292
this kind of level fulfillment has not yet happened yet.

22:23.312 --> 22:27.496
We have all sorts of struggles and our moments of beauty don't last.

22:27.537 --> 22:29.538
So how is this actually happening in this world?

22:30.459 --> 22:40.789
And I think we see this in this last set of images here where we find that Jesus is God the crucified Lion King.

22:42.131 --> 22:44.393
Jesus is God the crucified Lion King.

22:44.413 --> 22:46.455
Look with me back here, verse 11.

22:48.016 --> 22:49.778
Says,

22:49.922 --> 22:52.706
vine in his donkey's colt to the choice vine.

22:52.726 --> 22:57.033
He washed his garments and wine and his vestures and the blood of grapes.

22:58.976 --> 23:15.122
So this imagery kind of shifts again from this praise glorifying this divine kind of worship setting to this kingdom, Kingly conversation to this last imagery of vines and grapes, which is really imagery of abundance.

23:16.066 --> 23:19.751
Look, you see this donkey tied to the choices of vines.

23:22.134 --> 23:26.420
The reason why you wouldn't normally want to do this, because if you tied a donkey to choice of vines, what's that donkey going to do?

23:26.440 --> 23:27.662
It's going to eat all the vines.

23:27.902 --> 23:29.424
And you don't want to waste your choice of vines.

23:29.464 --> 23:30.906
But this is speaking to the abundance.

23:30.926 --> 23:33.930
Like, I don't even care if my donkey eats the nicest of my things.

23:34.371 --> 23:34.831
It doesn't matter.

23:34.851 --> 23:36.013
I got so much abundance.

23:36.053 --> 23:36.634
It doesn't matter.

23:36.674 --> 23:38.376
This is what this is.

23:38.416 --> 23:39.277
He's so prosperous.

23:39.297 --> 23:39.938
He doesn't care.

23:39.978 --> 23:41.841
So wealthy.

23:42.161 --> 23:44.104
He uses his finest grapes to do what?

23:44.865 --> 23:45.906
To wash his cloak.

23:46.722 --> 23:49.486
Which, and never mind the fact that that probably would make it more dirty.

23:49.547 --> 23:51.229
Let's just throw that out for a second.

23:51.930 --> 23:56.157
It's an insane thing to use your choices, your most expensive things to do that.

23:56.177 --> 24:01.105
It'd be like buying a bunch of Evion water, which I don't know if that's the most expensive water.

24:01.125 --> 24:03.750
It's the most expensive water someone like me can think of.

24:03.770 --> 24:06.514
And using that to like wash your car with, right?

24:07.375 --> 24:07.976
Be ridiculous.

24:08.016 --> 24:11.442
It'd be utterly wasteful.

24:12.002 --> 24:15.125
That's the kind of abundance and wealth that is being talked about.

24:15.145 --> 24:16.366
There's so much abundance.

24:16.386 --> 24:18.048
There's just wastefulness.

24:18.588 --> 24:20.410
Like I've been doing a lot of traveling last couple of weeks.

24:20.450 --> 24:24.694
And sometimes when I travel, I'll watch some of the dumb movies when I get too tired to read or try to work.

24:25.174 --> 24:26.396
And I know you all do it too.

24:26.416 --> 24:28.598
So don't look at me with those judgy eyes.

24:28.978 --> 24:30.600
We watch those dumb, dumb, dumb movies.

24:30.620 --> 24:37.886
And one of these movies, you know, this family's so wealthy that they go to this hotel and there's no place for them.

24:38.087 --> 24:41.650
And so the wife calls her husband and they buy the hotel.

24:42.050 --> 24:43.091
You know, why?

24:43.171 --> 24:44.212
Because they need a place to stay.

24:44.232 --> 24:44.813
They want to let them stay.

24:44.833 --> 24:45.353
They're so fine.

24:45.373 --> 24:47.555
I'll just buy the hotel and then you're going to have a place for me to stay.

24:47.936 --> 24:55.003
It's that kind of level of wealth and abundance that is just outside our, our even imagination is kind of what's being shown here.

24:55.583 --> 24:56.124
Abundance.

24:59.227 --> 25:03.952
But there's a second layer that even adds, I think another dimension to this abundance that we see.

25:05.773 --> 25:10.418
And it's that this is called like the blood of, of grapes on this cloak.

25:11.874 --> 25:16.719
It's another image where blood on garments is not a neutral image.

25:17.580 --> 25:19.723
There's multiple things happening, just like in good poetry.

25:19.743 --> 25:22.766
There's always multiple dimensions happening by certain images.

25:22.826 --> 25:32.357
And I think you see this that Joseph's cloak was stained with blood, the blood of goats, by Judas Hand.

25:33.358 --> 25:40.946
This is being brought back up again further in context of this abundance of these grapes,

25:41.282 --> 25:44.366
Blood itself is more of a limited resource, isn't it?

25:44.646 --> 25:49.072
Like you only have so much in your body, and if you lose too much, you're gonna die.

25:49.112 --> 25:50.975
You don't have unlimited blood.

25:52.136 --> 25:56.702
So what's this connection between this abundance and this grapes and this blood of grapes?

25:56.782 --> 26:03.992
And I think the fulfillment that happens throughout the Old Testament and the prophets help us understand these images more clearly.

26:04.012 --> 26:07.156
And this is just true of any kind of interpretation grid.

26:07.176 --> 26:08.978
If you wanna understand what the Bible's saying,

26:09.218 --> 26:13.784
Typically, you look at other places in the Bible that use the same language and it helps you understand it.

26:14.826 --> 26:22.717
And in Isaiah, the coming Savior is one whose robes are stained, the one who becomes a sacrifice for his people.

26:22.777 --> 26:35.495
He enters into the suffering of the people, the Lion King, full of strength and power and wealth and abundance, offers himself as a sacrifice.

26:35.515 --> 26:37.618
And what's wild about this is there's an abundance

26:37.986 --> 26:40.710
not just to his wealth, but his abundance to his blood himself.

26:42.213 --> 26:56.656
And Hebrews says that his blood is stronger than the blood of goats, that it's the last sacrifice needed, that Jesus the lion becomes a lamb, led to slaughter, that we might be washed and is ever-flowing blood.

26:58.799 --> 26:59.781
His blood is abundant.

27:01.664 --> 27:02.706
His grace is abundant.

27:02.746 --> 27:03.647
His mercy is abundant.

27:03.687 --> 27:05.490
It never runs out.

27:06.146 --> 27:08.528
So much so, it's almost wasteful.

27:09.269 --> 27:13.914
I would never call Christ blood wasteful, but that's the image that's being put forth.

27:13.934 --> 27:23.263
There's this cup that's constantly overflowing, never failing to cover every one of your sins, both now and anything that you do future, which there will be future sins for you.

27:23.283 --> 27:25.985
And me too, Christ blood has it.

27:26.005 --> 27:27.086
It doesn't run out of power.

27:28.067 --> 27:29.569
It's abundant.

27:29.589 --> 27:30.429
It is strong.

27:30.550 --> 27:31.350
It is mighty.

27:32.411 --> 27:35.154
This is the picture that has been put before us.

27:37.058 --> 27:45.089
That his blood has the power to fix not just you and not just the future you and not just the past you, but the generations to come.

27:45.890 --> 27:57.546
And not just humanity, but this whole world that is broken, the cosmic redemption that seated his blood is the one thing that is abundant and overflowing enough to handle it all.

27:59.148 --> 28:06.418
That is the image that's coming of the one that's going to come through your line, Judah, as abundant in strength, immersing, redemptive power.

28:07.074 --> 28:08.276
His power does not run out.

28:09.758 --> 28:14.985
Jesus is the coming God-lined King who is crucified for His people.

28:16.568 --> 28:24.679
That you might live in His kingdom, be called His sons, His daughters, His cup overflowed, overflows.

28:24.739 --> 28:25.801
It can fix any sin.

28:25.881 --> 28:27.243
It can heal any marriage.

28:27.784 --> 28:35.154
It can fix the decay in your bodies, which

28:35.394 --> 28:37.496
begs at least one question for us.

28:38.177 --> 28:45.826
Like we love these ideas and these hopes, but I have aches in my bodies now, so his blood didn't actually heal the aches in my body.

28:45.846 --> 28:54.376
How does his death, how does his sacrifice actually heal the world when we still experience pain?

28:56.739 --> 28:59.942
How does him dying actually fix this world?

29:00.863 --> 29:03.186
How does being crucified do this?

29:04.258 --> 29:06.080
Well, because he didn't stay dead, did he?

29:06.641 --> 29:07.783
He rose to new life.

29:09.004 --> 29:15.914
And I think in his resurrection, we get a picture for how we get to experience the same thing that he did.

29:15.994 --> 29:17.916
And I think at the end of this, we get a hint.

29:19.298 --> 29:24.686
And this is where I may or may not be stretching a little bit with the imagery, but I'm gonna go with it.

29:26.208 --> 29:32.736
Verse 12, it says, his eyes are darker than wine and his teeth wider than milk.

29:32.756 --> 29:33.938
This is one of the weirder

29:34.690 --> 29:39.054
phrases in this passage like, well, that's not how we talk about eyes and teeth usually.

29:39.074 --> 29:39.775
What's this about?

29:39.815 --> 29:42.778
Well, most people agree at least partly what this is about.

29:43.719 --> 29:54.810
It's about the vitality and strength of this king that you know, when someone's not doing well in life and they're maybe really sick or maybe if you've seen someone on their deathbed, one of the things you notice about them is they have weak eyes.

29:55.591 --> 29:56.632
Their eyes begin to fade.

29:57.573 --> 29:58.494
There's a weakness to them.

29:59.735 --> 30:02.258
This coming king

30:02.914 --> 30:13.749
His eyes darker than wine, meaning they're dark, they're strong, they're mighty, and their teeth are wider than milk, spring to the strength of his teeth, which is a sign of just general health.

30:16.754 --> 30:28.210
From blood-stained cloak to health and vitality, I think at least a little bit gives us a hint of death to life, that this coming king is gonna die

30:28.290 --> 30:30.414
but he's gonna rise again, resurrection.

30:30.434 --> 30:31.455
And why is this important?

30:31.475 --> 30:42.454
It's because this shows us the model and the method for how our world is made new and why we still experience pain in our day to day, although Christ is very much alive, sitting on his throne, working all things to this end.

30:42.514 --> 30:44.938
This is how the world is made new.

30:44.978 --> 30:50.067
Our world follows our great Lion King from death to resurrection.

30:51.549 --> 30:54.354
You have to go through death to get resurrection.

30:55.618 --> 31:06.090
And in our day-to-day lives, we experience many deaths, both physical deaths of seeing people we love die, spiritual deaths of dying to sin.

31:06.150 --> 31:10.295
There's all sorts of deaths that we have to go through.

31:11.216 --> 31:18.864
And not just you and me, but this whole world is going through a birthing process of death and resurrection, and we experience many birthing pains.

31:19.885 --> 31:23.890
But as our king is on the other side of death, risen to new life,

31:24.514 --> 31:25.916
so that it is our future promise.

31:26.837 --> 31:32.326
A promise that you don't get to fully inherit right now, but you will fully inherit one day.

31:32.366 --> 31:34.369
You get glimmers of this hope now.

31:34.409 --> 31:38.134
Now you see through the glass dimly, you get images of this.

31:38.655 --> 31:44.644
When you experience forgiveness, I mean, it's a beautiful image of the gospel that you get to taste of now.

31:44.684 --> 31:49.131
When you come to this table, you get to taste of the forgiveness Christ has for you, the grace that's abundant.

31:51.214 --> 31:53.778
So there's places where we get tastes of this.

31:55.458 --> 31:59.483
But this also ultimately points to the future when we get to taste it fully.

32:00.184 --> 32:04.249
When in death we get to inherit the life that is waiting for us forever.

32:06.172 --> 32:15.023
This tells us that this will happen and it's a surety because our Christ, our savior has gone before us.

32:15.103 --> 32:18.868
He's experienced death and he's risen again and now in him you too will as well.

32:22.012 --> 32:23.474
And so what this is meant to do

32:25.634 --> 32:26.575
is renew our hopes.

32:27.757 --> 32:41.916
We know our hopes that Jesus came as God, as King, and laid his life down that you could have life in him, and his blood is abundant to cover your sin.

32:43.899 --> 32:47.003
And he alone can lead you to the promise of eternal life.

32:48.044 --> 32:50.187
So follow him with much hope.

32:51.789 --> 32:55.154
This is true if you wander into this place that you've never

32:55.362 --> 32:59.046
experience faith in Jesus and you're curious about who this person is.

32:59.086 --> 33:00.047
This is true for you now.

33:00.087 --> 33:04.491
You can, you can call on him by faith and he will be yours and he will cover your sins.

33:06.353 --> 33:09.856
This is also true for you that have walked with the Lord for 50 years.

33:11.418 --> 33:14.060
There's a continual returning to the Lord that we need to have.

33:14.901 --> 33:17.624
We are quick to live by our own strength.

33:19.345 --> 33:21.147
This is telling us the futility of that.

33:22.708 --> 33:24.370
Your blood does not have the strength.

33:25.058 --> 33:26.680
to hold you, but Christ does.

33:26.701 --> 33:29.124
And He will only pours it out for you.

33:29.164 --> 33:30.967
Continually return to it.

33:31.368 --> 33:32.229
Renew your hope.

33:33.010 --> 33:40.682
May we walk in the hope of Christ our Redeemer and of the hope that He will renew our world.

33:41.944 --> 33:42.365
Pray with me.

33:47.833 --> 33:51.058
Holy God, we give you thanks for your mercy and your grace.

33:53.666 --> 33:57.032
I pray that you would renew our hope in you.

34:00.037 --> 34:09.273
To remember your glory, your goodness, your unwavering and abundant mercy that you have for your children, that we will cling to it.

34:10.415 --> 34:11.317
I pray this in your holy name.

34:11.777 --> 34:12.178
Amen.

